I won';t send you any internal messages if you prefer,,,,. I appreciate your work and effort.,, Darren and frankly the new people on board, are not questioning the topography they are questioning the fact that the land is only 45 feet  wide , with cliffs at both ends, not whether we can move dirt. I don't want you to be upset, the result  of the survey that you suggest, when I said that, THe response was they have been designing this point for about a year,Do you mean without a survey?). , Miles with a tape measure , could conclusively tell in 10 minutes the distance from cliff edge to cliff edge.. I  have not seen the drawing , but doesn't it include the height of land on which it should be built? I was told it said 25 feet . CAll me   I also approved the guermantes  notary moving forward.  With regard the office plan, Doug (my doug) ,  j;ust told me, ( I just hung up)  that he is coming down here, because it seems the office has to be redesigned from "SCRATCH" , as jp's
 office was  simply trying to fit the old plan on a site that  can't support it.  Now it's my turn  Frustrating  isn't it.  you and I should speak

----- Original Message ----
From: "jpm6929@aol.com" <jpm6929@aol.com>
To: jeeproject@yahoo.com
Sent: Friday, February 2, 2007 6:44:11 PM
Subject: Unaceptable comments














